# competition-system

Core Competition Management Components:

1. Competition Types (Importance: 85/100)
- Weekend challenges (48-hour duration)
- Weekly competitions (Monday-Sunday)
- Monthly competitions (calendar month)
- Custom duration events with configurable start/end
- Maximum 10 active competitions per user per day

2. Scoring System (Importance: 90/100)
- Ring-based scoring:
  * Move ring: 1 point per closure
  * Exercise ring: 2 points per closure
  * Stand ring: 1 point per closure
- Daily maximum: 4 points total
- Bonus point for closing all rings
- Streak multiplier: +0.5x per consecutive day

3. Competition Status Management (Importance: 80/100)
- Status transitions:
  * Draft -> Scheduled
  * Scheduled -> Active
  * Active -> Completed
  * Active -> Cancelled (requires premium)
- Automatic status updates based on time
- Grace period: 24 hours for late joins
- Early exit penalties for non-premium users

4. Leaderboard System (Importance: 85/100)
- Real-time ranking updates
- Position change notifications
- Daily progress indicators
- Underdog detection for close competitions
- Tie-breaking rules:
  * Most ring closures
  * Earliest completion time
  * Random if still tied

5. Participant Management (Importance: 75/100)
- Minimum 2 participants
- Maximum based on subscription tier:
  * Free: 5 participants
  * Mover: 15 participants
  * Crusher: Unlimited
- Auto-removal after 3 days of inactivity
- Re-join restrictions: Once per competition

6. Competition Rules (Importance: 80/100)
- Single active competition per type
- Cooling period between competitions: 24 hours
- Minimum duration: 24 hours
- Maximum duration: 31 days
- Required goal settings:
  * Move goal (calories)
  * Exercise minutes
  * Stand hours

